15/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Boris Trajkovski met on Tuesday (14 October) with his Montenegrin counterpart, Filip Vujanovic. 
The two leaders reiterated their countries' readiness to combat international terrorism, and agreed to send a joint request to UNMIK regarding the opening of a corridor connecting Macedonia and Montenegro via Kosovo. 
They also agreed to accelerate the procedure for establishing a Macedonian consulate in Podgorica and to plan a trilateral meeting involving Macedonia, Montenegro and Albania in the Montenegrin capital. 
Trajkovski is to lead a business delegation to Montenegro by year's end. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 15/10/03; MIA, Makfax - 14/10/03)
